# Skill Evals — {{project.name}}

Test your AI agent skills to verify they activate correctly and produce expected output.

## Quick Start

```bash
# Run evals for a specific skill
python3 .ai/evals/run_eval.py mnemix-memory --platform codex

# Grade the results
python3 .ai/evals/grade_eval.py mnemix-memory/iteration-1

# View benchmark
cat .ai/evals/mnemix-memory/iteration-1/benchmark.json
```

## Supported Platforms

| Platform | Command |
|----------|---------|
| **Codex** | `python3 .ai/evals/run_eval.py <skill> --platform codex` |
| **Claude Code** | `python3 .ai/evals/run_eval.py <skill> --platform claude` |
| **Copilot / Cursor** | Manual — see [Semi-Automated Flow](#semi-automated-flow) |

## Semi-Automated Flow

For platforms without CLI exec (Copilot, Cursor):

1. View the eval metadata: `cat .ai/evals/<skill>/eval_metadata.json`
2. Paste each test prompt into the agent chat
3. Copy the full chat transcript into `.ai/evals/<skill>/iteration-<N>/eval-<name>/with_skill/transcript.md`
4. Run the grader: `python3 .ai/evals/grade_eval.py <skill>/iteration-<N>`

## Custom Test Cases

Add your own test cases without conflicting with toolkit-provided ones:

1. Create `.ai/evals/<skill>/custom_evals.json` using the same format as `eval_metadata.json`
2. The runner automatically loads both files and merges test case arrays
3. Your custom evals are never touched by toolkit upgrades

```json
{
  "skill_name": "mnemix-memory",
  "evals": [
    {
      "id": 100,
      "name": "my-custom-test",
      "prompt": "Your custom test prompt here",
      "expected_output": "What you expect the agent to do",
      "files": [],
      "assertions": [
        {
          "id": "custom-check",
          "type": "deterministic",
          "check": "transcript_contains",
          "pattern": "pattern-to-find",
          "description": "What this checks"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

## Assertion Types

| Type | `check` values | Graded by | Use for |
|---|---|---|---|
| `deterministic` | `transcript_contains`, `transcript_not_contains`, `transcript_order` | Regex | Protocol compliance, command execution |
| `llm-judge` | Free-text criteria | Model call (Phase 2) | Quality, completeness, style |

## File Structure

```
.ai/evals/
├── run_eval.py                      ← Eval runner
├── grade_eval.py                    ← Grading engine
├── README.md                        ← This file
├── .gitignore                       ← Ignores iteration-*/ results
└── <skill-name>/
    ├── eval_metadata.json           ← Toolkit-provided test cases (auto-upgraded)
    ├── custom_evals.json            ← Your custom test cases (never touched)
    └── iteration-<N>/               ← Results (gitignored)
        ├── eval-<case-name>/
        │   ├── with_skill/
        │   │   ├── transcript.md
        │   │   ├── timing.json
        │   │   └── grading.json
        │   └── without_skill/
        │       └── ...
        └── benchmark.json
```
